| Redis Cluster | G-Counter (approximate) | Distributed counters |
| Riak | OR-Set, PN-Counter, LWW-Register | General KV store |
| Automerge / Yjs | CRDT sequences | Collaborative text editing |
| Figma | Custom CRDT | Real-time multiplayer design |

## Interview Q&A

**Q: When would you NOT use a CRDT?**
A: When you need exact, strongly-consistent values — bank account balances, unique usernames, inventory counts that must not go negative. CRDTs trade precision for availability.

**Q: What is the difference between a CRDT and operational transformation (OT)?**
A: OT (used by Google Docs) transforms operations relative to concurrent edits and requires a central server to sequence operations. CRDTs work peer-to-peer without a server; each replica converges independently.
